    <title>Are you ready for the government’s move to Agile?</title>
    <link>/drupal-govcon-2016/drupal-govcon-2016/sessions/are-you-ready-government%E2%80%99s-move-agile</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The White House’s United States Digital Service (USDS) is actively working with government agencies to make it easier than ever to buy Agile software development.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this session, strategists from the USDS will discuss how procurement reforms currently underway will fundamentally transform how the government builds and buys more than $80 billion in IT each year, which may have a huge impact on the Drupal community.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The session will include background on how and why federal government is moving forward fixed price, examples of recent Agile contracts, and case studies of successful Agile projects in the public sector. Additionally, we’ll discuss how Drupal companies can leverage existing resources and find out how to better engage with the federal government on this massive opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Learning Outcomes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of the new Agile procurement initiatives driving innovation within government&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;Overview of the USDS TechFAR Handbook &amp;amp; Digital Services Playbook&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;Resources to learn more about partnering with the government on large and impactful projects&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Beginner&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;AaronPava&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-timeslot field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Time Slot(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots clearfix&quot; class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
